revisions.description: The private MIB module definition for the Dell PowerConnect Devices. This MIB allows PowerConnect devices to be integrated into Dell ITA management system.

powerConnectVendorMIB.description: Adding new objects - Dell PPID, Revision, Express Service Code.

EnvMonState.name: EnvMonState
EnvMonState.description: Represents the state of a device being monitored. Valid values are: normal(1): the environment is good, such as low temperature. warning(2): the environment is bad, such as temperature above normal operation range but not too high. critical(3): the environment is very bad, such as temperature much higher than normal operation limit. shutdown(4): the environment is the worst, the system should be shutdown immediately. notPresent(5): the environmental monitor is not present, such as temperature sensors do not exist. notFunctioning(6): the environmental monitor does not function properly, such as a temperature sensor generates a abnormal data like 1000 C.

productIdentificationDescription.name: productIdentificationDescription

productIdentificationBuildNumber.name: productIdentificationBuildNumber

productIdentificationURL.name: productIdentificationURL

productIdentificationPerUnitTable.name: productIdentificationPerUnitTable
productIdentificationPerUnitTable.description: Identification specific to product instance and, in case of stackable products, per unit. If the product is not stackable, it will be considered a stack of one unit and therefore this table will contain one conceptual row only.

productIdentificationPerUnitEntry.name: productIdentificationPerUnitEntry
productIdentificationPerUnitEntry.description: This row applies to a unit in a stackable product.

productIdentificationPerBoxIndex.name: productIdentificationPerBoxIndex
productIdentificationPerBoxIndex.description: The index of the stack unit to which this conceptual row corresponds. Note that the index will be the same index as the index of a 'chassis' physical entity in the entity MIB of the product.

productIdentificationChassisServiceTag.name: productIdentificationChassisServiceTag
productIdentificationChassisServiceTag.description: Chassis Service tag of the product.

productIdentificationBootromVersion.name: productIdentificationBootromVersion
productIdentificationBootromVersion.description: The boot image version of the product.

productIdentificationPiecePartID.name: productIdentificationPiecePartID
productIdentificationPiecePartID.description: The piece part id of the product.

productIdentificationPPIDRevision.name: productIdentificationPPIDRevision
productIdentificationPPIDRevision.description: The PPID revision of the product.

productIdentificationExpressServiceCode.name: productIdentificationExpressServiceCode
productIdentificationExpressServiceCode.description: The express cervice code of the product.

productIdentificationBannerMotdAckMode.name: productIdentificationBannerMotdAckMode
productIdentificationBannerMotdAckMode.description: If enable is selected, user will be required to acknowledge the banner displayed on the console. The user would have to type 'y' or 'n' to continue to the login prompt. If n is typed, the session is terminated and no future communication is allowed on that session. However, serial connection will not get terminated if user does not enter 'y'. Use disable option to disable banner acknowledge.

productStatusGlobalStatus.name: productStatusGlobalStatus
productStatusGlobalStatus.description: Current status of the product.This is a rollup for the entire product. The status is intended to give initiative to a snmp monitor to get further data when this status is abnormal. This variable can take the following values: 3: OK If fans and power supplies are functioning and the system did not reboot because of a HW watchdog failure or a SW fatal error condition. 4: Non-critical If at least one power supply is not functional or the system rebooted at least once because of a HW watchdog failure or a SW fatal error condition. 5: Critical If at least one fan is not functional, possibly causing a dangerous warming up of the device.

productStatusLastGlobalStatus.name: productStatusLastGlobalStatus
productStatusLastGlobalStatus.description: The status before the current status which induced an initiative to issue a global status change trap.

productStatusTimeStamp.name: productStatusTimeStamp
productStatusTimeStamp.description: The last time that the product global status has been updated. The time will be given in TimeTicks

productStatusGetTimeOut.name: productStatusGetTimeOut
productStatusGetTimeOut.description: Suggested time out value in milliseconds for how long the SNMP getter should wait while attempting to poll the product SNMP service.

productStatusRefreshRate.name: productStatusRefreshRate
productStatusRefreshRate.description: Rate in seconds at which the SNMP service cached data is being updated.

productStatusGeneratingTrapsFlag.name: productStatusGeneratingTrapsFlag
productStatusGeneratingTrapsFlag.description: Indicates if this SNMP service is generating SNMP Traps. This variable can take the following values: 1: true - The device is capable and currently configured to generate traps if necessary. 2: false - The device is not capable of generating traps. 3: disabled - The device is capable but not configured to generate traps.

envMonFanStatusTable.name: envMonFanStatusTable
envMonFanStatusTable.description: The table of fan status maintained by the environmental monitor. Not Supported by Dell Modular Blade Server switches.

envMonFanStatusEntry.name: envMonFanStatusEntry
envMonFanStatusEntry.description: An entry in the fan status table, representing the status of the associated fan maintained by the environmental monitor. Not Supported by Dell Modular Blade Server switches.

envMonFanStatusIndex.name: envMonFanStatusIndex
envMonFanStatusIndex.description: Unique index for the fan being instrumented. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning. Not Supported by Dell Modular Blade Server switches.

envMonFanStatusDescr.name: envMonFanStatusDescr
envMonFanStatusDescr.description: Textual description of the fan being instrumented. This description is a short textual label, suitable as a human-sensible identification for the rest of the information in the entry. Not Supported by Dell Modular Blade Server switches.

envMonFanState.name: envMonFanState
envMonFanState.description: The mandatory state of the fan being instrumented. Not Supported by Dell Modular Blade Server switches.

envMonFanSpeed.name: envMonFanSpeed
envMonFanSpeed.description: Speed of the fan being instrumented. Not Supported by Dell Modular Blade Server switches.

envMonSupplyStatusTable.name: envMonSupplyStatusTable
envMonSupplyStatusTable.description: The table of power supply status maintained by the environmental monitor card.

envMonSupplyStatusEntry.name: envMonSupplyStatusEntry
envMonSupplyStatusEntry.description: An entry in the power supply status table, representing the status of the associated power supply maintained by the environmental monitor card.

envMonSupplyStatusIndex.name: envMonSupplyStatusIndex
envMonSupplyStatusIndex.description: Unique index for the power supply being instrumented. This index is for SNMP purposes only, and has no intrinsic meaning.

envMonSupplyStatusDescr.name: envMonSupplyStatusDescr
envMonSupplyStatusDescr.description: Textual description of the power supply being instrumented. This description is a short textual label, suitable as a human-sensible identification for the rest of the information in the entry.

envMonSupplyState.name: envMonSupplyState
envMonSupplyState.description: The mandatory state of the power supply being instrumented.

envMonSupplySource.name: envMonSupplySource
envMonSupplySource.description: The power supply source. unknown - Power supply source unknown ac - AC power supply dc - DC power supply externalPowerSupply - External power supply internalRedundant - Internal redundant power supply

envMonSupplyCurrentPower.name: envMonSupplyCurrentPower
envMonSupplyCurrentPower.description: Current power consumption of the power supply being instrumented. 0 - indicates that Current power is not available for related supply.

envMonSupplyAveragePower.name: envMonSupplyAveragePower
envMonSupplyAveragePower.description: Average power consumption of the power supply being instrumented. 0 - indicates that Average power is not available for related supply.

envMonSupplyAvgStartTime.name: envMonSupplyAvgStartTime
envMonSupplyAvgStartTime.description: The power supply data start. 0 - indicates that power and related start time is not available for supply.
